Subject: Formal Complaint Regarding Dental Treatment and Service Experience

To Prodental Specialists Group,

I am writing to express my deep dissatisfaction and disappointment regarding the treatment and service I have received at your clinic.

When I first visited your clinic, I came prepared with a referral letter and X-rays from another clinic. My main concern was to get braces, and I was hoping for a clear treatment plan and guidance. However, I was advised by Dr. [Name] to begin by treating my gum disease before proceeding with braces. Trusting your expertise, I followed the recommendation and began the treatment.

To date, I have spent over $4,000 and several months undergoing treatment, only to be told recently that I will need to wait another four months before a final decision can be made regarding braces. What‚Äôs more distressing is that during a consultation with the braces specialist, I was informed that the estimated cost of the full procedure‚Äîincluding retainers, consultations, scaling, and X-rays‚Äîwould be approximately $20,000 to $25,000.

Had this information been shared with me at the beginning‚Äîespecially by the braces specialist‚ÄîI would have had the opportunity to consider all my options, whether to continue treatment with your clinic or seek more affordable alternatives elsewhere. Despite the high cost, I chose to proceed because I trusted that I would receive professional care and see positive results. Unfortunately, that has not been the case.

I want to make it clear that I have all recordings, videos, and receipts from day one until today as documentation of my entire experience. This situation has not only affected me financially but also caused me significant emotional stress. I feel misled and extremely disappointed.

I hope you take this matter seriously and provide a clear explanation and resolution. If this issue is not addressed appropriately, I will have no choice but to consider further action.

Sincerely,
Kayalvizhi Amurthalingam

reviews.name: Kai
reviews.text:
I visited Asiaa Dental Clinic yesterday for a teeth whitening session, along with scaling, polishing, and an additional tooth filing procedure. My friend recommended me as she was quite pleased with their treatment. I was attended to by Dr Thasha, and I must say‚ÄîI‚Äôm thoroughly impressed with both her and the team‚Äôs overall service and attitude.

Dr Thasha was patient and attentive, clearly explaining each step of the procedures beforehand. Throughout the session, she and the staff consistently checked in to ensure I was comfortable and doing well.

During the second stage of the whitening treatment, I experienced an unexpected reaction‚Äîintense numbness and a burning sensation on my lips, which left me panicking as it was something I‚Äôd never felt before. The staff responded immediately, informing Dr Thasha, who attended to me promptly. She remained calm and professional, reassuring me that some patients may have such reactions when the lips come into contact with the chemical. She also explained that the severity of the reaction can vary between individuals. My lips were visibly swollen and appeared burned by the end of the session, but Dr Thasha comforted me that it will disappear after 1-2 days and reduced the duration for the final stage of the treatment to prevent further discomfort. She also told me to contact them if the condition doesn't improve.

Unfortunately, shortly after the session, I experienced sudden and intense sharp pain in the bottom front row of my teeth. Dr Thasha checked in on me, and I informed her about the pain. She kindly provided ibuprofen, which helped relieve the pain slightly. I was also given fluoride mousse and a soothing gel for my teeth and lips to bring home for aftercare.

What truly touched me was the follow-up‚Äîa WhatsApp message from the clinic the next day to check if I was feeling better. Their care and concern really stood out to me.

While the reaction and pain I experienced were likely due to my naturally sensitive teeth, I am still very pleased with the service provided. I highly recommend Asiaa Dental Clinic for their professionalism, warm service, and affordable pricing. The location is also relatively close to KSL (about 10mins walk), although do note that certain part of the clinic is currently undergoing renovation.

Thank you Dr Thasha and the team :)
